text: Frederick Mair (15 April 1901 - 25 December 1959) was an Australian cricketer. He played twenty-two first-class matches for New South Wales between 1933/34 and 1937/38. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1901 births Category:1959 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Sydney
